      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "chopped"
    },
    {
      "name": "Beurre-monte",
      "amount": "2 tablespoons",
      "notes": "see notes for preparation"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the Binchotan grill to 450F (230C).",
    "In a large clay pot or Dutch oven, heat the olive oil over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the crushed tomatoes, vegetable broth, Tunisian spice blend, and sea salt. Stir to combine.",
    "Add the split black cardamom pods and bring the mixture to a simmer.",
    "Transfer the pot to the preheated Binchotan grill and cook for 20-25 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened and the cardamom pods are tender.",
    "Remove the pot from the grill and stir in the chopped parsley and beurre-monte. ",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
  ],
